Tom,<br><br>
Thanks for such an eloquent post.  Your brothers, members of the pack,  me are not tolerant of you.  They and I respect you for who and what your are.  Respect is something that is earned and not given.<br><br>
I have never liked War, but have accepted that history has proven it will happen.  I do not want my sons in War or to see them die with honor in some far off place.  They saw the price I paid in my profession and did not want to share in it.  I deeply respect that decision as I would anyone elses.<br><br>
I still participate in this war machinery thing.  It is my career and my life.  My flying career is all I could have dreamed it could be.  Privileged to have served and still do.  The support of this pack I work with, many foreign, and some ex Vietnamese Officers exist in harmony.  I do not know what it is like to fight for acceptance.  AS with you other opinions are heard, digested, and stored, but I try to not let them destabilize my harmony with my self. Probably one of the most important reasons I have my inner peace.<br><br>
The Venom that Spatz has spewed forth on this site was meant for me and not the rest.  I pushed his button.  It was no accident.<br><br>
If he or anyone else has that message for me they need to keep it off this site.  Intensity is welcome in my view, but burining rage and hate is not.<br><br>
Silent Warrior (SW) spawned from my profession not just from some macho desire.  Sorry history named us.<br><br>
PS<br><br>
Doc.  My E-mail is listed.  If you have something to say, say it.  
